    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1951-11-01T11:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1951-11-01T11:00:00-05:00" n="46"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d46">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">320/11–151: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the Netherlands</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Chapin</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">The Hague</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1951-11-01T17:00:00+01:00"
                            >November 1, 1951—5 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>432. Re <gloss target="#t_Deptel1">Deptel</gloss> 556, October 25, 9 p. m. In
                    election fill Yugo <gloss target="#t_SC1">SC</gloss> seat Neth <gloss
                        target="#t_del1">del</gloss> instructed by cab decision vote for Sov
                    satellite or Greece depending how situation develops in <gloss target="#t_UNGA1"
                        >UNGA</gloss>. Neth inclined support Sov satellite for fol reasons: <list>
                        <label>1.</label>
                        <item>Gentlemen’s agrmnt with USSR made at Yalta and San Francisco 1945
                            assuring Sovs additional seat <gloss target="#t_SC1">SC</gloss>.</item>
                        <label>2.</label>
                        <item>To support Greece, Philippines or other noncandidate regarded as
                            provocative to USSR.</item>
                        <label>3.</label>
                        <item>Election this state regarded as not sufficiently important to argue
                            about.</item>
                    </list>
                </p>
                <p>Prelim mtg West Eur reps held London October 26 to discuss <gloss target="#t_UN1"
                        >UN</gloss> agenda in accord Neth position this point. Only Belg inclined
                    support Greece.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Chapin</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
